reviewText: I don't typically like reality TV.  Mostly because there are far to many obnoxious people on the shows.  Duck Dynasty is the exception.  It was quite by accident that I happen to flip to it one day while looking for something to watch.  After only a few minutes of watching how a father was concerned about his daughter dating a boy and how he handled it,  I was hooked. They may poke a little fun at one another, but they're not cruel or condescending.  Overall they actually seem pretty wise about life and know how to be good to each other.  The other real difference is they screw up once in awhile like most guys, and the results are often funny rather than hurting anyone.  Talk about a refreshing difference.  So if your going to watch reality TV I suggest this show.  You might actually learn something good from these bearded duck hunters and their families.CA Luster

reviewText: These guys manage to do what they do without selling-out. They resisted pressure to up ratings (not like they need it!) with cussing, unabashedly are people of faith & family, and it's great to see 'em using the fruits of the land ;) which may offend some people, but such is life. Authenticity is worth its weight in gold and is as rare as duck teeth.Phil Robertson, the Dynasty Godfather is blessed with more charisma that most humans. The "Robertson Zone" lifts viewer's spirits, with wholesome, eccentric-American fun. "I'm a jack of all trades and a Renaissance Man - ain't nothin' I can't do," rightfully declares Uncle Si.  This is one smart clan! We appreciate the delightful matriarch and fine cook, Miss Kay; Papa Phil likes a woman with a little meat on her bones who can cook real food. He dispenses valuable advice to his grandsons on finding the right woman, "When you're talking 'bout bees, dogs, or women, pain can come up on you real fast." That man has a voice made for listening to, he could say anything and make it compelling. Willie, Jase, Si, Jep, and employees Martin and Godwin are an awesome, hilarious team.Approximately 286 Minutes Feature Run Time Includes:Driving Miss SadieSi-YonaraThe Grass & The FuriousFowl PlaySweatin' BulletsTruck CommanderDuck No, We Won't GoSpring Pong CleaningGood Morning, West MonroeSamuri SiOf Mattresses and MenDrag Me to GloryI'm Dreaming of a Redneck Christmasand Bonus Footage: Pizza vs. Toast; Mountain Man; The Brains Behind the Duck; Bootleg Building; Catch Phrases, and (HILARIOUS, should be on MTV) Work Hard, Nap Hard - Si + music

reviewText: When I first heard about Duck Dynasty, I did not know what to think because I was hearing about it from other people.  I watched my first episode about a year ago and I did not like it, I thought it was stupid and a waste of TV channel space.  Well, it grew on me.  I think Duck Dynasty is so funny.  Uncle Si never fails to say something stupid or something that will stick with you for a while.  For example, his old girlfriend breaks up with him and tells Si "it's not you, it's me.  Si responds, you darn right it's you ya heifer."  Classical Si quote.  Even though this is one of the most redneck families I have ever watched, I do enjoy watching their family dynamics.  The wives are all very good looking, but yet doesn't seem like they are with their men for money.  The wives seem more high maintenance.  I enjoy watching the men hunt and do stupid stunts during their work hours.  I really enjoyed watching them make a redneck water park.  Duck Dynasty might seem very immature and stupid to some people, but really its funny and a good comedy show for adults.
summary: We all need a little redneck in our lives

reviewerName: Shana "That's my opinion- I could be wrong!"
reviewText: I was channel surfing and I accidently came across "Duck Dynasty", purely out of curiousity I checked it out. Now it's me and my husband's favorite show. Are you sick of TV shows that use foul language and filth to get laughs? Yes? Then check out "Duck Dynasty". If you have grew-up in the country or live in the country than you will really relate to this family. Our family laughs out loud threw the whole show, I love that these are people who don't take themselves too seriously. This is a show that we can watch with the whole family even with the kids and not worry that it's going to be inappropriate content.What I really love about this show is that they end every show around the dinner table as a family and with a prayer. Every show has a great moral of some sort. I love everyone Mrs. Kay, Phil, Jase, Uncle Si (crazy like a fox son!) and Willie and their other family too.One reason I love the ending of this show is that it reminds me of growing up with my grandparents and us all around the table as a family. Just my opinion that that's how families stay close by setting around the table with one another in fellowship. This show brings those great memories back.
summary: Great family show, Great moral values
